@NODE Installation
@TITLE "au.player · Installation"


    @{b}Installation@{ub}


    Copy au.player to players/ subdirectory of your AmiNetRadio
    installation. Restart AmiNetRadio if required.

    Make sure au.player has a higher priority than the 
    mpeg.player, this can avoid possible problems with mpega.library 
    false detecting Sun/ NeXT Audio files as mpeg streams (you can set 
    priority by editing/ creating the <player>.pri files).


@ENDNODE

@NODE FAQ
@TITLE "au.player · FAQ"


    @{b}Frequently Asked Question@{ub}


    Q: I have a file which is not detected at all.

    A: It's probably a broken file which misses necessary and
       important information. Unsupported files are usually
       detected, but not played.


    Q: When I play 8khz (or smaller) samples I have weird breaks
       in the output.

    A: Use a normal AHI Unit and not the music unit, seems to be 
       a bug in AHI or AmiNetRadio.


    Q: I have a very short sample, when I have repeat enabled
       everything seems to lock up.

    A: This is a problem with AmiNetRadio 3.1. Don't use repeat
       on very small files ( < 1 seconds) for the time beeing.


    Q: I have a relatively short file ( < 1 second). It looks 
       like it's played, but I don't hear anything or just a 
       short 'cluck'.

    A: That's because the sample is too short and therefore the
       buffers of AmiNetRadio are not completly filled. You can
       try to reduce the Audio-Buffer in AmiNetRadio Audio-
       Settings to a smaller value. AmiNetRadio is a streaming
       application and therefore this behavior is normal.


@ENDNODE

@NODE bugs
@TITLE "au.player · Known Bugs"


    @{b}Known Bugs@{ub}


    no bug is currently known. :)



    BUT if au.player fails to dedect a Sun/ NeXT Audio file and it 
    falls back to mpeg.player it can happen that AmiNetRadio likes 
    to crash or to do other weird things. It's some problem in the 
    used mpega.library which detects too many files as mpeg stream.
    
    So when you want to report a au.player crash make sure you
    test w/o mpeg.player installed temporaly.

    (And after this: Don't use the not properly detected Sun/ NeXT
    Audio file ;)


@ENDNODE

